properties.areaDesc: West Slopes South Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 21 at 12:04AM PST until January 22 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected above 3000 feet. Total snow accumulations
of 6 to 18 inches.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Snohomish and King
Counties, including Snoqualmie Pass and Stevens Pass. Cascade
mountains and valleys of Pierce and Lewis Counties, including
the Crystal Mountain Ski Area, Paradise on Mount Rainier.

* WHEN...From 4 AM early this morning to 4 AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Heaviest snow amounts at Stevens Pass and
Paradise at Mount Rainier. Snoqualmie Pass may see a rain and
snow mix tonight.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM EARLY THIS MORNING TO 4 AM PST WEDNESDAY ABOVE 3000 FEET
